Manage scheduled cron jobs (Sprint 5 §1)

Usage: cron <COMMAND>

Commands:
  list    List every scheduled job (id, label, schedule, status, next-fire-at, last-fired-at, fire
          count)
  add     Add a new job. Schedule grammar: a duration (`30m`, `2h15m`), a 5-field cron expression
          (`*/15 * * * *`), or an RFC 3339 timestamp (`2026-05-20T14:30:00Z`)
  pause   Pause a job. `next_fire_at` is preserved; resuming a paused job fires immediately if its
          fire-time was reached during the pause window
  resume  Resume a paused job
  remove  Remove a job from the scheduler
  status  Show one job's full record (status, payload, fire history)
  edit    Edit a job's label and/or schedule. Pass `--label` to rename, or `--schedule` to change
          cadence. Changing the schedule recomputes `next_fire_at` from the new grammar against the
          current clock
  run     Fire a job immediately, bypassing its scheduled time. The cap-gate is still applied: a job
          whose `payload_caps` aren't in the live kernel grant is refused (and marked `Failed`)
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help
